President Donald Trump has announced his intention to designate John Barsa as the Acting Administrator of the United States Agency for International Development (USAID). Barsa is currently serving as the Assistant Administrator for USAID's Bureau for Latin America and the Caribbean, focusing on democracy-related programs in Venezuela, Nicaragua, and Cuba. Prior to this role, Barsa held various leadership positions in the Department of Homeland Security and served in the United States Army Reserves. He has also worked for a Florida representative and held external engagement roles in the National Aeronautics and Space Administration and the Department of Homeland Security. Barsa is a graduate of Florida International University.